<?xml version="1.0"?>
<html>
  <problem>
    <img src="/static/problems/MIT/boriskor/BKimages/rolling disc attached to rotating pulley.png" alt="Rolling down an incline disc is attached to a rotating pulley" encrypturl="no"/>
    <parameter default="2" description="Maximum Number of Tries" type="int_pos" name="maxtries" loncapaid="11"/>
    <br/>
    
      <p>
A thin light string is wrapped around a solid uniform disk of mass \(M\) and radius \(R\), mounted as shown. The loose end of the string is attached to the axle of a solid uniform disc of mass \(m\) and the same radius \(r\) which is can roll down without slipping down an inclined plane that makes angle \(\theta\) with the horizontal. Find the acceleration \(a\) of the rolling disc. Neglect friction in the axle of the pulley.
</p>
    
    <br/>
    <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="yes" loncapaid="12" type="MultipleChoice">
      <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
        <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">

                a = (2mg sin \(\theta\))/(M + 2m)          
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">

                a = (mg cos \(\theta\))/(M + 3m)          
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">

                a = (2mg sin \(\theta\))/(2M + 3m)          
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="true">

                a = (2mg sin \(\theta\))/(M + 3m)          
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">

                a = (mg cos \(\theta\))/(2M + m)          
        </choice>
      </choicegroup>
    </multiplechoiceresponse>
      </problem>
</html>
